SystemDesign Concepts

Consistency Models -> 
1. Strong Consistency, 
2. Casual Consistency(Causal consistency is slightly weaker than strong consistency. 
It ensures that if a read or write causally depends on a previous write, then any replica that serves the dependent operation 
will first apply that earlier write. In this way, the system preserves the correct cause-and-effect relationships between operations, 
without requiring full synchronization across all replicas.)
3. Eventual Consistency

Key primitives for coordination across services:-
1.Leader election
2. Distributed Locks -> pessimistic lock(Acquire lock first) , optimistic lock(perform action first and check later)
3. Consensus Protocol -> Paxos and Raft
4. Service Discovery

